---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="UK Campus Based PhD — Years 2 to Completion | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="After Year 1 (the Extended Advanced Diploma) online with Brenkley Doctoral College, PhD Year 2 onward is UK campus based at your chosen partner university, through to PhD graduation — normally at the end of Year 3 for full-time students.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme &mdash; PhD Year 2 Onward</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">UK Campus Based PhD &mdash; Years 2 to Completion</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">PhD Year 2 to Graduation &mdash; UK Campus Based &mdash; Partner University</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">Once you complete Year 1 — the <a href="/programmes/mphil/" class="text-accent underline">Extended Advanced Diploma</a> — online with Brenkley Doctoral College, PhD Year 2 onward moves to a UK campus. You study in person at your chosen partner university, through to thesis completion, viva voce, and graduation, normally at the end of Year 3 for full-time students.</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mt-4">Articulation from Year 1 into PhD Year 2 is via your chosen partner university's own admissions and articulation process. International researchers can move to the UK for this stage under a Student (CAS) visa sponsored by the partner university.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Year 2 → Completion</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Full-time or part-time study at your partner university, through to thesis and viva</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">UK Campus Based</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">In-person study, supervision, and facilities at your chosen partner university's UK campus</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">CAS Visa Route</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">International researchers can move to the UK under a Student visa sponsored by the partner university</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Set by University</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Year 2 onward fees are set independently by your chosen partner university, not by Brenkley Doctoral College</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Moving to Campus</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">From Online Year 1 to UK Campus Life</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Year 1 with Brenkley Doctoral College is entirely online, so researchers anywhere in the world can complete the Extended Advanced Diploma without relocating. PhD Year 2 onward is different by design: you join your chosen partner university's UK campus in person, with face-to-face supervision, access to campus library and research facilities, and a resident cohort of doctoral researchers.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Exactly what campus-based study involves — attendance expectations, office or desk space, induction, and researcher community — is set by your chosen partner university, since they deliver and award Year 2 onward.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Brenkley Doctoral College's role in this stage is to prepare you well in Year 1 and to support a smooth articulation into the partner university you choose.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Your Visa &amp; Arrival</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Supported by Your Partner University</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">If you are an international researcher moving to the UK for PhD Year 2, your chosen partner university handles your visa sponsorship directly. Once they confirm your place, they issue a Certificate of Acceptance for Studies (CAS), which you use to apply for a UK Student visa.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Because Year 1 is completed online, you only need to arrange your move to the UK once your Year 2 place is confirmed — there is no need to relocate earlier than necessary.</p>
          <div class="card mt-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Same qualification, campus-delivered:</strong> The PhD awarded at the end of this pathway is conferred by your partner university to the same standard as their other doctoral researchers — with the added foundation of the SCQF-rated Extended Advanced Diploma behind you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Year 2 and Year 3, On Campus</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Once Year 1 (the Extended Advanced Diploma) is complete, PhD Year 2 and Year 3 are delivered entirely by your chosen partner university, on their UK campus.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Year 2: Inquiry</h3>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Delivered by your partner university — UK campus based</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Admission via the partner university's articulation process into PhD Year 2</li>
            <li>Arrival and induction on campus (CAS visa route for international researchers)</li>
            <li>Advanced methods training and campus research facilities</li>
            <li>Data collection in professional or campus-based context</li>
            <li>Data analysis and emerging findings</li>
            <li>Peer research seminar presentation</li>
            <li>Annual Review</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Year 3: Completion</h3>
          <p class="text-xs font-medium text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Delivered by your partner university — UK campus based</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Thesis writing with in-person supervisor feedback cycles</li>
            <li>Academic writing support</li>
            <li>Pre-submission panel review</li>
            <li>Thesis submission</li>
            <li>Viva voce examination, on campus</li>
            <li>Award of PhD by the partner university</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Progression -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Getting Here</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">From Online Year 1 to UK Campus Completion</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8 max-w-3xl">This pathway starts with Year 1 — the Extended Advanced Diploma, completed entirely online with Brenkley Doctoral College. On successful completion, you choose which partner university you progress to, articulating directly into PhD Year 2 on their UK campus and continuing through to PhD graduation, normally at the end of Year 3 for full-time students.</p>
      <div class="card max-w-3xl mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">UK Student (CAS) visa route:</strong> Because Year 1 is delivered entirely online, international researchers can complete it from anywhere in the world. When you progress to PhD Year 2, your chosen partner university sponsors a UK Student visa (via a Certificate of Acceptance for Studies) so you can study on their campus.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Choice of institution:</strong> Brenkley Doctoral College maintains progression arrangements with a network of partner universities. You select the institution that best fits your research area, career goals, and circumstances — final admission is confirmed through each university's own admissions and articulation process, not guaranteed automatically.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Before You Progress</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What You Need for Year 2</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Extended Advanced Diploma</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Successful completion of Year 1 with Brenkley Doctoral College — SCQF Level 11, 180 credits, including the applied internship.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Partner University Admission</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Acceptance through your chosen partner university's own admissions and articulation process — not guaranteed automatically by completing Year 1.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">UK Student (CAS) Visa</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">For international researchers relocating to a UK campus, a Certificate of Acceptance for Studies sponsored by your partner university, used to apply for a UK Student visa.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">English Language</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Set by your chosen partner university — typically IELTS 6.5 overall or equivalent for international researchers whose first language is not English.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Start with Year 1, online</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">This UK campus-based pathway begins with Year 1 — the Extended Advanced Diploma, delivered entirely online. Apply now to start your research journey, with a clear route to a UK campus and PhD graduation.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Apply now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Ask us anything</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
